main event: A witness observed a whitish, disc-shaped object that kept appearing and disappearing while moving rapidly in the sky over Dayton, Ohio in 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as moving very, very fast and was not very high up in the sky.
The object appeared to change position rapidly, appearing in one place and then another.
The witness observed the object through the windshield and possibly some chemicals.
The object changed brightness and appeared to disappear and reappear.
The sighting lasted for approximately 3 minutes.
